{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a minimum trainee teacher wage equivalent to Teaching Assistant salary",
        "additional_details": "Full-time trainees work in schools while paying \u00a39,250 in fees, leaving many in financial hardship. We believe this could discourage talented individuals from entering teaching, worsening teacher shortages. We believe a minimum trainee wage equivalent to a Teaching Assistant salary could make training more accessible, reduce financial stress, and help recruit and retain high-quality teachers. We believe the Government must act now to support future educators and protect education standards.",
        "background": "We want the Government to introduce a minimum trainee teacher wage that is equivalent to a Teaching Assistant salary. Many trainees work full-time while paying \u00a39,250 in fees, making teaching inaccessible for many. We believe this could ease teacher shortages and the financial strain on trainees.",
